content:
Not sure if this is useful, but wanted to note that RLA showed no log output here: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/82993#issuecomment-796279820

Probably the algorithm just didn't pick up on the error for some reason or another. The error in the full logs was:

 error[E0425]: cannot find value `e` in this scope
  --> src/librustdoc/html/sources.rs:62:29
   |
62 | ...                   e
   |                       ^ help: a local variable with a similar name exists: `_e`

error: aborting due to previous error

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0425`.
error: could not compile `rustdoc`

And here's a link to the logs: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/82993/checks?check_run_id=2081786831
